    • Uses of I_DnaThing in thing.dna

      Subinterfaces of I_DnaThing in thing.dna 
      Modifier and Type Interface Description
      interface  I_MappedDna
      All Genetic objects have a length in the number of loci they've got, but they also can have a "virtual length", as if Genes are located at various points along the genome.
      Classes in thing.dna that implement I_DnaThing 
      Modifier and Type Class Description
      class  C_Chromosome
      A single "strand" of genes, capable of being mutated and crossed over with another single strand (another chromosome)
      NOTE: map locations are currently not checked for sequential ordering, so each new Gene that is added must be at a higher map location than all of the previously added Genes.
      class  C_ChromosomePair
      A Chromosome pair is just two chromosomes of a diploid genome.
      class  C_XsomePairMicrosat
      Class of one type of chromosome pairs to keep safe the Chromosomes class.
      class  C_XsomePairSexual
      chromosome pair in charge of sex affairs
